<TITLE> PepsiCo to build $170 mln Russia snack plant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ST PETERSBURG, Russia, June 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - PepsiCo International said on Saturday it would build a snacks production plant in the Russian town of Azov and invest $170 million over five years in the project. The project, which would create 1,000 jobs, is PepsiCo's second major manufacturing investment in Russia, where it already operates a $160 million plant in Kashira, near Moscow
